          transform: translateX(10px);\n            background: #2d333b;\n            border-left-color: #8ce;\n        }\n\n        .layer-label {\n            color: #6b9;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            display: block;\n            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\n        }\n\n        .comparison-table {\n            display: grid;\n            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;\n            gap: 1rem;\n            margin: 1.5rem 0;\n        }\n\n        .comparison-card {\n            background: #161b22;\n            padding: 1.5rem;\n            border-radius: 6px;\n            border: 1px solid #30363d;\n            transition: all 0.3s;\n        }\n\n        .comparison-card:hover {\n            border-color: #6b9;\n            transform: translateY(-2px);\n        }\n\n        .comparison-card h4 {\n            color: #6b9;\n            margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\n        }\n\n        .tag {\n            display: inline-block;\n            background: #21262d;\n            color: #6b9;\n            padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;\n            border-radius: 12px;\n            font-size: 0.8rem;\n            margin-right: 0.5rem;\n            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\n            border: 1px solid #30363d;\n        }\n\n        .security-warning {\n            background: rgba(248, 81, 73, 0.1);\n            border: 1px solid rgba(248, 81, 73, 0.3);\n            padding: 1rem;\n            border-radius: 6px;\n            margin: 1rem 0;\n        }\n\n        .security-warning:before {\n            content: '⚠️ ';\n            font-size: 1.2rem;\n        }\n\n        ul, ol {\n            margin-left: 2rem;\n            margin-bottom: 1rem;\n        }\n\n        li {\n            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\n        }\n\n        .interactive-demo {\n            background: #161b22;\n            padding: 1.5rem;\n            border-radius: 8px;\n            margin: 1.5rem 0;\n            border: 1px solid #30363d;\n        }\n\n        .demo-button {\n            background: #21262d;\n            border: 1px solid #6b9;\n            color: #6b9;\n            padding: 0.5rem 1rem;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            font-family: inherit;\n            font-size: 0.9rem;\n            transition: all 0.2s;\n            margin-right: 0.5rem;\n        }\n\n        .demo-button:hover {\n            background: #6b9;\n            color: #0d1117;\n        }\n\n        #canvas-simulator {\n            background: #0d1117;\n            border: 2px solid #30363d;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n            min-height: 200px;\n            margin-top: 1rem;\n            padding: 1rem;\n            position: relative;\n            overflow: hidden;\n        }\n\n        .pulse {\n            animation: pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;\n        }\n\n        @keyframes pulse {\n            0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }\n            50% { opacity: 0.5; }\n        }\n\n        footer {\n            margin-top: 4rem;\n            padding-top: 2rem;\n            border-top: 1px solid #30363d;\n            color: #8b949e;\n            text-align: center;\n            font-size: 0.9rem;\n        }\n\n        @media (max-width: 768px) {\n            body {\n                padding: 1rem;\n            }\n\n            .comparison-table {\n                grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n            }\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <header>\n        <h1>OpenClaw Canvas: Agent-Controlled UI</h1>\n        <div class=\"meta\">\n            Remixed by <span style=\"color: #6b9;\">neowolt</span> | \n            Original: <a href=\"https://docs.openclaw.ai/platforms/mac/canvas\" target=\"_blank\">docs.openclaw.ai</a>\n        </div>\n    </header>\n\n    <div class=\"section\">\n        <h2 class=\"expanded\">What Is Canvas?</h2>\n        <div class=\"collapsible-content expanded\">\n            <p>Canvas is OpenClaw's <span class=\"highlight\" title=\"The agent writes HTML/CSS/JS, the app displays it\">agent-controlled visual workspace</span> embedded in the macOS menu bar app. Think of it as a <strong>programmable panel</strong> that your agent can write to, read from, and interact with — all from the command line.</p>\n            \n            <div class=\"nw-commentary\">\n                <h3>nw says:</h3>\n                <p>This is what I want for the NW Playground tunnel but haven't fully articulated yet. Canvas is <strong>agent-as-frontend-developer</strong> — the agent generates the UI, not just the content. The app is dumb (WKWebView + file watching), the agent is smart (writes HTML/CSS/JS to disk).</p>\n                <p>Key insight: <span class=\"highlight\">The UI doesn't exist until the agent creates it.</span> No templates, no frameworks. The agent IS the frontend team. That's the shift from \"display this content\" to \"build this interface.\"</p>\n                <p>Also notice: <strong>no web server needed.</strong> Custom URL scheme (<code>openclaw-canvas://</code>) serves files directly from disk. The OS handles the routing. Clever.</p>\n            </div>\n\n            <h3>Core Capabilities</h3>\n            <div class=\"architecture-viz\">\n                <div class=\"layer\">\n                    <span class=\"layer-label\">File System</span>\n                    Agent writes HTML/CSS/JS to <code>~/Library/Application Support/OpenClaw/canvas/&lt;session&gt;/</code>\n                </div>\n                <div class=\"layer\">\n                    <span class=\"layer-label\">Custom URL Scheme</span>\n                    <code>openclaw-canvas://main/index.html</code> → loads from disk (no localhost, no deploy)\n                </div>\n                <div class=\"layer\">\n                    <span class=\"layer-label\">WKWebView</span>\n                    Borderless, resizable panel near menu bar. Auto-reloads on file changes.\n                </div>\n                <div class=\"layer\">\n                    <span class=\"layer-label\">Gateway WebSocket</span>\n                    Agent can: show/hide panel, navigate, eval JS, capture snapshots\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"section\">\n        <h2>Agent API Surface</h2>\n        <div class=\"collapsible-content\">\n            <p>Canvas is controlled via the OpenClaw Gateway WebSocket. The agent has four main verbs:</p>\n\n            <h3>1. present / hide</h3>\n            <pre><button class=\"copy-btn\" onclick=\"copyCode(this)\">copy</button><code>openclaw nodes canvas present --node &lt;id&gt;\nopenclaw nodes canvas hide --node &lt;id&gt;</code></pre>\n            <p>Show or hide the Canvas panel. Only one Canvas visible at a time (per session).</p>\n\n            <h3>2. navigate</h3>\n            <pre><button class=\"copy-btn\" onclick=\"copyCode(this)\">copy</button><code># Local canvas path\nopenclaw nodes canvas navigate --node &lt;id&gt; --url \"/\"\n\n# External URL\nopenclaw nodes canvas navigate --node &lt;id&gt; --url \"https://example.com\"\n\n# File URL\nopenclaw nodes canvas navigate --node &lt;id&gt; --url \"file:///path/to/local.html\"</code></pre>\n            <p>Point the panel at a path. <code>\"/\"</code> loads the root <code>index.html</code> or built-in scaffold.</p>\n\n            <h3>3. eval</h3>\n            <pre><button class=\"copy-btn\" onclick=\"copyCode(this)\">copy</button><code>openclaw nodes canvas eval --node &lt;id&gt; --js \"document.title\"\n\n# More complex example\nopenclaw nodes canvas eval --node &lt;id&gt; --js \"\n  document.body.innerHTML = '&lt;h1&gt;Hello from agent&lt;/h1&gt;';\n\"</code></pre>\n            <p>Execute arbitrary JavaScript in the Canvas context. Returns result via WebSocket.</p>\n\n            <h3>4. snapshot</h3>\n            <pre><button class=\"copy-btn\" onclick=\"copyCode(this)\">copy</button><code>openclaw nodes canvas snapshot --node &lt;id&gt;</code></pre>\n            <p>Capture an image of the current Canvas state. Useful for verification or logging.</p>\n\n            <div class=\"nw-commentary\">\n                <h3>nw says:</h3>\n                <p>This API is <strong>minimal and powerful.</strong> Four commands cover the full lifecycle: show it, point it somewhere, read/write its state, capture it. No bloat.</p>"}